PRIVACY POLICY
This Privacy Policy ("Policy") is an integral part of our Terms of Service and applies to all websites, mobile applications, and other software applications (collectively, the "Services") developed, operated, or maintained by CodingShadows - owned by Rusu Dinu-Ștefan ("we," "us," "our," or "Data Controller"). Contact email: dinu@codingshadows.com. By using our Services, you explicitly consent to the collection, use, and transfer of your data as described in this
        Policy.
SCOPE AND CONSENT
This Policy applies to all information collected through our Services, regardless of the method of collection, type of device, platform, or method of access. By using our Services, you irrevocably consent to the collection, processing, storage, and potential transfer of your data as described in this Policy. If you do not agree with any aspect of this Policy, you must immediately cease using our Services.
TYPES OF DATA COLLECTED
We collect and process various categories of data across all our Services (websites, mobile applications, and other software applications), including but not limited to:
• Personal Data: email addresses, names, phone numbers, and any other information you voluntarily provide
• Usage Data: IP addresses, browser type, device information, operating system, access times, screens visited, and interaction patterns
• Location Data: approximate location derived from IP address or
        precise location if explicitly permitted
• Technical Data: crash reports, performance metrics, system logs, and device-specific information
• User Content: any content, materials, or information you submit or make available through the Services
• Metadata: information about how you use the Services, including interaction patterns and preferences
• Third-Party Data: information received from third-party services and APIs Our Services integrate with third-party services
        including but not limited to:
• Google Crashlytics
• Firebase Crashlytics
• Firebase Performance
• AdMob
• Analytics providers
• Authentication services These third parties may collect additional data according to their own privacy policies across both our websites and mobile applications. We expressly disclaim responsibility for their data collection practices while reserving the right to receive and process any data they share with us.
LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING
We process your data under one or more of the following legal bases:
• Your explicit consent
• Performance of a contract
• Compliance with legal obligations
• Protection of vital interests
• Legitimate business interests
• You acknowledge that by using our Services, you grant us implicit consent to process your data for any purpose reasonably connected to providing, improving, or maintaining the Services.
DATA USAGE AND PROCESSING
We use collected data across all our Services (websites, mobile applications, and other software) for purposes including but not limited to:
• Providing and maintaining the Services
• Improving user experience
• Analytics and performance monitoring
• Marketing and communication
• Legal compliance and enforcement
• Security and fraud prevention
• Application crash analysis and debugging
• User behavior analysis and service
        optimization You explicitly acknowledge and agree that we may use any collected data, including User Content, for machine learning, artificial intelligence training, and service improvement purposes without additional notification or compensation, regardless of which of our Services the data was collected from.
DATA RETENTION AND DELETION
We retain your data for as long as necessary to provide our Services or comply with legal obligations. You may request deletion of your personal data, but you acknowledge that:
• Some data may be retained for legal compliance
• Anonymized or aggregated data may be retained indefinitely
• Backup copies may persist for a reasonable period
• Data shared with third parties may be retained by them
• User Content may be retained as per our Terms of
        Service
SECURITY MEASURES
We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect your data. However, no security system is impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee absolute security. You acknowledge and accept this inherent risk when using our Services. In the event of a data breach, we will notify affected users as required by applicable law.
INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. By using our Services, you consent to such transfers and acknowledge that different countries may have different data protection standards.
SPECIAL ACCESS USERS
Users with special access privileges (including beta testers, early access users, and internal testers) acknowledge and agree that:
• Additional data may be collected for testing and development purposes
• Their usage patterns and feedback may be more closely monitored
• They are bound by stricter confidentiality obligations as detailed in our Terms of Service
• Their data may be retained for extended periods for development purposes
LEGAL ACTIONS AND COMPLIANCE
We may use your data for legal purposes, including:
• Responding to legal requests
• Enforcing our terms and policies
• Protecting our rights and interests
• Complying with legal obligations You explicitly consent to the disclosure of your data to law enforcement or other authorities when required by law or when we believe disclosure is necessary to protect our rights or the safety of others.
CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We reserve the right to modify this Policy at any time without prior notice. Continued use of our Services after any changes constitutes acceptance of the modified Policy. We may, but are not obligated to, notify you of significant changes.
CONTACT INFORMATION
For any questions about this Policy or our data practices, contact us at dinu@codingshadows.com. While we will make reasonable efforts to respond to your inquiries, we reserve the right to prioritize responses based on business needs and legal requirements.
LEGAL INFORMATION
This Privacy Policy complies with:
• EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
• California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
• EC Directive 95/46/EC
• Directive 2002/58/EC as revised by Directive 2009/136/EC This Policy was last updated: October 2024